item.title: Muammar Gaddafi: Obituary
item.description:
Muammar Gaddafi: Obituary
A senior National Transitional Council official has said that deposed Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi has died of his wounds after being captured near his hometown of Sirte. Muammar Gaddafi came to power in 1969 in a coup at the age of 27 and went on to rule Libya for 42 years with an iron fist. He has left Libya in tatters and despite the vast oil wealth, a vast majority of Libyans still live on about $2 a day and 40 per cent remain unemployed. Gaddafi wanted to be the leader of the Arab world and modeled himself on Egyptian leader Gamal Abdel Nasser. He published the Green Book which established rule of the people but in reality he exercised absolute power. The former Libyan leader was accused of bombing Pan Am Flight 103 in Scotland, a charge he always denied. After this Libya remained under internatinal isolation for years. When the uprising gathered momentum earlier this year he blamed everyone, from US to al-Qaeda, and called the protesters rats and cats of Libya. Many will remember Gaddafi as the leader who set Libya back by many years.

item.description:
Gaddafi 'killed, died of wounds': Video of Sirte celebrations
For latest updates, follow RT on http://twitter.com/RT_com and http://www.facebook.com/RTnews Colonel Gaddafi has reportedly been captured alive, after two months on the run. The country's new authorities claim the ousted leader's been taken in his hometown of Sirte, reportedly overrun by government forces. It's been the last major stronghold of Gaddafi's supporters for the past two months. Reporters in Sirte have so far been unable to confirm Gaddafi's capture, or even that the town has fallen to interim forces. Libya's current ruling body, the National Transitional Council, had said they would declare Libya liberated, once Sirte falls.

item.description:
MUAMMAR GADDAFI KILLED IN GUNBATTLE - LIVE VIDEO
CVB NEWS- Libya's ousted leader Colonel Muammar Gaddafi reportedly has been captured in his hometown of Sirte. The reports came after transitional forces claimed control of Sirte, following weeks of fierce fighting. Libyan media has said that Gaddafi died in the fierce gun battle, But these reports have not been confirmed. There are several stories about Gaddafi's death. Some say he was shot dead in the bunker where he was hiding while others say he was captured while he was trying to escape in a convoy. His last words reportedly were " don't shoot". Colonel Gaddafis capture has ended months of conflict in Libya

item.title: Video e vrasjes së Gedafit
item.description:
Video e vrasjes së Gedafit
Muammar Gheddafi është vrarë. Lajmi është konfirmuar zyrtarisht nga Këshilli Nacional i Tranzicionit, qeveria tranzitore libiane. Sipas zyrtarëve të KNT, vdekja e Gedafit ka ndodhur si pasojë e plagëve të marra gjatë operacionit për kapjen e tij. Al Jazeera, e cila citon 2 burime të ndryshme, bën të ditur se koloneli është vrarë gjatë një shkëmbimi zjarri. Sipas Tv Libya, Gedafi është vrarë me një plumb në kokë. "Koloneli është kapur në një vendstrehim në Sirte dhe para luftëtarëve të Këshillit Nacional të Tranzicionit ka thirrur: "Mos qëlloni, mos qëlloni"", bëjnë të ditur forcat rebele që kanë marrë nën kontroll fortesën e fundit të kolonelit. Sipas TV Libya, edhe djali i Gedafit, Mutassim, dhe shefi i shërbimeve sekrete të regjimit, Abdallah Senoussi, janë arrestuar. Ndërkohë, në rrugët e qyteteve libiane janë derdhur me mijëra njerëz, të cilët kanë nisur festimet. Atmosfera po përcillet nga televizioni libian.
